sentences: Tim Wessel Vanhamel (born 11 December 1977 in Zonhoven, Belgium) is a Belgian rock musician who has been a member of and performed with a number of bands including Evil Superstars, Deus and Eagles of Death Metal.
In 1995, at the age of 17, Vanhamel joined Evil Superstars as their guitarist.
He played for the band until their split in 1998.
He then played in Deus for a short time during their 'Ideal Crash' tour in 1999.
In 2000, Vanhamel began recording the debut for his own band, Millionaire.
In 2007, Millionaire contributed to the soundtrack for the film "Ex-Drummer" based on the novel by the Flemish author Herman Brusselmans.
He recorded a solo album in 2007.
The full album Welcome to the Blue House was released 31 January 2008.
In 2008, he contributed guest vocals to Millionaire bandmate Aldo Struyf's side-project, Creature with the Atom Brain.
He also toured as part of Eagles of Death Metal in their early days.
After its release the band started playing on summer festivals such as Marktrock among with other bands and Flip Kowlier as the Ex-Drummer band.
